SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR
Once you plug in the generic linear demand function \(Q(p) = a + b p \), the elasticity function has the form: \( E(p) = \frac{b p}{a-b p}\).  

$PAR 

\(\frac{dE}{dp} = \frac{b(a-bp)+b^2p}{(a-bp)^2}\)
$PAR \( =  \frac{ab}{(a-bp)^2}\)

$PAR
\(\frac{d^2E}{dp^2} = \frac{2ab^2}{(a-bp)^3}\).

Both \(\frac{dE}{dp}\) and \(\frac{d^2E}{dp^2}\) are always positive for \(0 \le p \le \frac{a}{b}\) the elasticity function is increasing a concave up.  Thus graph B is the correct answer.

END_SOLUTION
